<item>
            <title>[DERBY-5196] Correct the layout of log.ctrl as described on the Derby web site</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/DERBY-5196</link>
                <project id="10594" key="DERBY">Derby</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The Derby web site describes the layout of the log control file, log.ctrl, here: &lt;a href=&quot;http://db.apache.org/derby/papers/logformats.html#Format+of+Log+Control+File&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://db.apache.org/derby/papers/logformats.html#Format+of+Log+Control+File&lt;/a&gt; This description does not agree with the format actually produced by LogToFile.writeControlFile(). That format can be examined using the ControlFileReader tool attached to &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/DERBY-5195&quot; title=&quot;Create tools for browsing the files in the database log directory.&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;DERBY-5195&quot;&gt;DERBY-5195&lt;/a&gt;. The description on the web site should be corrected.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12504399">DERBY-5196</key>
            <summary>Correct the layout of log.ctrl as described on the Derby web site</summary>
